<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🏰 Builder Basics — The Living Village (Extension · Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Bring It All Together · <strong>Course:</strong> Builder Basics · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Type:</strong> Extension Activity · <strong>Time:</strong> about 40 minutes</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🧩 A bonus challenge, not a weekly lesson. Try it after <strong>Complete Your Village</strong>.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · The Challenge 🎯</h2>
<p>Make your village feel <strong>alive</strong> — with crops, animals, and water. It must have <strong>all eight</strong> of these:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🌾 Farm
🏠 Farm house
🗼 House with a watchtower
🧱 Fence
💧 Pond with fish
🌉 Bridge over the pond
🪣 Well
🐄 A few animals</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>One rule: build with… Circle one:</strong> code · your hands</p>
<p><strong>Tick each one when it is done in your world:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>☐ 🌾 Farm
☐ 🏠 Farm house
☐ 🗼 House with a watchtower
☐ 🧱 Fence
☐ 💧 Pond with fish
☐ 🌉 Bridge over the pond
☐ 🪣 Well
☐ 🐄 A few animals</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>2 · Match It 🔗</h2>
<p><strong>A farm is made of rows of… Circle one:</strong> crops · doors · lava</p>
<p><strong>A watchtower is a tower that is… Circle one:</strong> tall · flat · underground</p>
<p><strong>A bridge goes over the… Circle one:</strong> pond · roof · farm</p>
<p><strong>Fish live in the… Circle one:</strong> pond · fence · well</p>
<hr />
<h2>3 · Use a Loop 🔁</h2>
<p>A loop repeats the same step again and again.</p>
<p><strong>Which one is best made with a loop? Circle one:</strong> one animal · a row of crops · one block</p>
<p><strong>A fence has four sides. Between each side, the agent must… Circle one:</strong> turn · stop · fly away</p>
<hr />
<h2>4 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Go to your world. Build them with code: the <strong>farm</strong>, <strong>farm house</strong>, <strong>watchtower house</strong>, <strong>fence</strong>, <strong>pond with fish</strong>, <strong>bridge</strong>, and <strong>well</strong>. Then add a <strong>few animals</strong>.</p>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> (a phone is fine). Show two things:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Say these out loud, filling in the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
